    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "# Publish the content calendar with MySQL and WordPress without manual work for Cross-Posting\n\n**Pattern:** Social Scheduler · **Level:** Production · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nPublish the content calendar with MySQL and WordPress without manual work for Cross-Posting. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual cross-posting is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nWeekly Schedule → Normalize Post Payload → Build the Brief → Draft with AI Writer → Refine with AI Editor → Publish Draft to WordPress → Load Previous Snapshot → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to social scheduler without manual effort\n- Anyone automating cross-posting in marketing\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Standardizes the process every time\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google AI API key; Google OAuth2 / service account; MySQL connection; Slack OAuth2; WordPress credentials.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.",
        "width": 480,
        "height": 900
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -830,
        80
      ],
      "id": "33c2e992-727f-79de-5ac6-b7d041b01d87",
      "name": "📘 Workflow Overview"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 3
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        -230,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "be75bf25-d93d-9e93-0e65-bc5703071c0a",
      "name": "🛟 Error handling & retries"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🤖 AI cluster\n\nPurple nodes form one AI unit: the root node orchestrates, sub-nodes plug in via typed ports (model / memory / tools / parser). Swap the chat model without rewiring anything else. Costs scale with tokens — keep prompts lean and cap iterations.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 6
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
      "position": [
        190,
        -20
      ],
      "id": "409d3b9e-b5eb-1972-f0de-28a8a73a5dcf",
      "name": "🤖 AI cluster"
    },
    {
      "parameters": {
        "content": "## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your cross-posting process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.",
        "width": 360,
        "height": 260,
        "color": 4
      },
      "type": "n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote",
      "typeVersion": 1,
